                    <abstract lang="eng">The article discusses the chemical-pharmaceutical industry in Germany based on the assumption that there is a niche or hidden market driving its growth. Topics include the structure of the industry that is dependent on multinational enterprises and small firms, the role of innovations in industry growth and risks involved in engaging in international trade. A study which explored the existence of hidden markets which effect trends, field of applications and critical success factors is offered.</abstract>
